The foregoing summary, as well as the following detailed description of the preferred embodiments, is better understood when read in conjunction with the appended drawings. For the purpose of illustrating the invention, there is shown in the drawings embodiments that are presently preferred, it being understood, however, that the invention is not limited to the specific methods and instrumentalities disclosed. In the drawings:


FIG. 1 is a perspective view of a data storage device, or disk drive, in which the present invention is embodied;


FIG. 2 is a perspective view of a disk cartridge for use with the disk drive of the FIG. 1;


FIG. 3 is a bottom view of the disk cartridge of FIG. 2;


FIG. 4 is a top view of the disk drive of FIG. 1 with a top cover of the device housing removed;


FIGS. 5 and 6 are top views of the disk drive of FIG. 4 illustrating the insertion of a disk cartridge into the disk drive;


FIG. 7 is a perspective view showing the upper surface of a movable platform of the disk drive of FIG. 4;


FIG. 8 is a perspective view showing the lower surface of the movable platform of FIG. 7;


FIG. 9 is a perspective view of an interchangeable guide rail that can be used to implement both guide rails of FIG. 4;


FIGS. 10A and 10B illustrate the change in elevation of the movable platform of FIG. 7 as the platform moves from a first position to a second position;


FIGS. 11A and 11B are perspective views of a latch member in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 12A shows the latch member of FIGS. 11A and 11B in an unlocked, open position with position with respect to the guide rail of FIG. 10;


FIGS. 12B and 12C show the latch member of FIGS. 11A and 11B in an unlocked, natural bias position with respect to the guide rail of FIG. 10;


FIGS. 12D and 12E show the latch member of FIGS. 11A and 11B in a locked position with respect to the guide rail of FIG. 10; and


FIGS. 13 and 14 illustrate the operation of the latch member of FIG. 11A and 11B.
